							</author>
							<locus n=""/>
							<title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Maslak al-muttaqīn</title>
							<title xml:lang="per">مسلك المتقين</title>
							<note>
								<p>A lengthy didactic poem on aspects of theology and law by Ṣūfī
									Allāhyār (or Ilāhyār) Khan Bukhārī (fl. 1050/1640). </p>
								<p>Contents: introduction, on Islamic doctrine, and four books
									concerning purification, ritual prayer, zakāt and fasting
									according to Ḥanafī fiqh. </p>
								<p>Book 1 was completed in 1111/1699, Book 2 the following year.</p>
								<p>Colophon, f. 396v. Copied at the Ādīnah (Friday) Madrasa at
									Faizabad, in Badakhshan, Afghanistan, by Ḥabīb Allāh ibn Mullā
									‘Āshūr Muḥammad. Completed at breakfast time on Friday 19 Ṣafar 1284/22 June 1867. </p>
								<p>Other contents: front endpaper and f. 1r, owners’ scribbles; 1r,
									ownership inscription dated 1339/1920-21; 396v, note of a
									payment and a bayt of verse.</p>
							</note>
							<textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
